H0.text: Which word derives from the Greek words for ‘star’ and ‘sailor’. Astronaut

H1.text: Which word derives from the Greek words for ‘star’ and ‘sailor’. Stellarnav

H2.text: Which word derives from the Greek words for ‘star’ and ‘sailor’. Cosmonaut

H3.text: Which word derives from the Greek words for ‘star’ and ‘sailor’. Rednaut

A4.text: An astronaut (from the Ancient Greek ἄστρον (astron), meaning 'star', and ναύτης (nautes), meaning 'sailor') is a person trained, equipped, and deployed by a human spaceflight program to serve as a commander or crew member of a spacecraft.

A5.text: Cosmonaut (from the Russian 'kosmos' (космос), meaning 'space', also borrowed from Greek κόσμος).
